# Firebase Configuration
# Create a Firebase project at https://console.firebase.google.com
# Enable Authentication (Google provider) and Firestore Database

VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your_project_id.firebaseapp.com
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your_project_id
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your_project_id.firebasestorage.app
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=your_messaging_sender_id
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=your_app_id

# ─── Deployment Setup ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Copy this file to .env and fill in your Firebase credentials
# 2. Add these as GitHub Secrets (Settings → Secrets → Actions)
# 3. In Firebase Console → Authentication → Settings → Authorized domains
#    Add: fsalamoni.github.io
#    Add: www.protagonistarpg.com.br
# 4. In Firebase Console → Firestore → Create database (start in production mode)
#    Apply the rules from firestore.rules
# 5. The site is served at:
#    https://fsalamoni.github.io/omniforge/         (GitHub Pages, direct)
#    https://www.protagonistarpg.com.br/omniforge/  (via Cloudflare Worker proxy)
# See README.md for full Cloudflare + Firebase setup instructions.
